ruck, mit der sie die eigene wie die gegnerische Religionspartei belegten. In dieser aufgeheizten Situation war an eine konstruktive Arbeit auf den Reichsta-gen kaum zu denken. Um die Handlungsfähigkeit des Reiches zu erhalten, musste man also einen Sprachgebrauch entwickeln, der eine zielführende Kommunikation zwischen den Ständen aller Konfessionen überhaupt erst ermöglichte - ein Drahtseilakt zwischen politischer Rücksichtnahme und religiösem Selbstverständnis.  aIn the Imperial Diets of the Protestant Reformation period, Catholic and Protestant factions stood in opposition to each other. Both sides claimed to represent Christian truth. For the Holy Roman Empire to maintain any capacity for action, people had to develop a way of speaking that allowed for communication between representatives of all faiths – a high-wire act at the intersection between political considerations and religious self-conception.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristian literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aChristian sectszEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aChristianity and politicszEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aCommunication in politicszEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aIdentification (Religion)xHistoryy16th century. 0aProtestantszEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aReformation. 4aBegriffsgeschichte. 4aKonfessionalisierung. 4aReformationsgeschichte. 4aReichstag. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aHistory of the Reformation.  aImperial Diet.  aconceptual history.  aconfessionalization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2014z978311